text: Many of the objects in the PCC Buckets and PCC Products data model includes a field for storing miscellaneous data. The field is called Misc and has the type map<string, any> . Even though the Misc field is stated to support storing values of type any there are some limitations to what type the values can have. The following types can be used: bigint bitset boolean byte bytearray char date float/ double int ipaddress long short string
